In comparisonto parents in the control group, parents in the experimen-tal (intervention) group engaged in significantly less harshparenting practices and reported better parent–child rela-tionships. There are some factors that shed light on thesefindings. It has been well documented that Hong KongChinese parents are influenced by the social-cultural em-phasis on obedience, social conformity and academic per-formance [39]. Consequently, many parents in Hong Kongengage in harsh parenting practices in rearing their chil-dren.
